{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2063,"text":"That splendid music, the coming-in music,"},{"time":5000,"text":"\"The Elephant March\" from \"Aida,\"\nis the music I've chosen for my funeral."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10905,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":12000,"text":"And you can see why. It's triumphal."},{"time":17000,"text":"I won't feel anything, but if I could,"},{"time":21000,"text":"I would feel triumphal\nat having lived at all,"},{"time":25000,"text":"and at having lived\non this splendid planet,"},{"time":27120,"text":"and having been given\nthe opportunity to understand"},{"time":30257,"text":"something about why I was here\nin the first place, before not being here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37448,"text":"Can you understand\nmy quaint English accent?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":41891,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":44651,"text":"Like everybody else, I was entranced\nyesterday by the animal session."},{"time":49750,"text":"Robert Full and Frans Lanting and others;"},{"time":55213,"text":"the beauty of the things that they showed."},{"time":57463,"text":"The only slight jarring note was when\nJeffrey Katzenberg said of the mustang,"},{"time":63000,"text":"\"the most splendid creatures\nthat God put on this earth.\""},{"time":66855,"text":"Now of course, we know\nthat he didn't really mean that,"},{"time":70480,"text":"but in this country at the moment,\nyou can't be too careful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73657,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":75000,"text":"I'm a biologist, and the central theorem\nof our subject: the theory of design,"},{"time":82000,"text":"Darwin's theory of evolution\nby natural selection."},{"time":86723,"text":"In professional circles everywhere,\nit's of course universally accepted."},{"time":91000,"text":"In non-professional circles\noutside America, it's largely ignored."},{"time":97000,"text":"But in non-professional\ncircles within America,"},{"time":101000,"text":"it arouses so much hostility --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":104000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":105100,"text":"it's fair to say that American biologists\nare in a state of war."},{"time":111000,"text":"The war is so worrying at present,"},{"time":112999,"text":"with court cases coming\nup in one state after another,"},{"time":115596,"text":"that I felt I had to say\nsomething about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"If you want to know what I have\nto say about Darwinism itself,"},{"time":122000,"text":"I'm afraid you're going\nto have to look at my books,"},{"time":125000,"text":"which you won't find\nin the bookstore outside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":131467,"text":"Contemporary court cases"},{"time":133000,"text":"often concern an allegedly\nnew version of creationism,"},{"time":137000,"text":"called \"Intelligent Design,\" or ID."},{"time":141000,"text":"Don't be fooled.\nThere's nothing new about ID."},{"time":145149,"text":"It's just creationism under another name,"},{"time":148523,"text":"rechristened --\nI choose the word advisedly --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":151905,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":153000,"text":"for tactical, political reasons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155000,"text":"The arguments of so-called ID theorists"},{"time":157000,"text":"are the same old arguments\nthat had been refuted again and again,"},{"time":160396,"text":"since Darwin down to the present day."},{"time":163908,"text":"There is an effective evolution lobby"},{"time":167000,"text":"coordinating the fight\non behalf of science,"},{"time":169120,"text":"and I try to do all I can to help them,"},{"time":172000,"text":"but they get quite upset\nwhen people like me dare to mention"},{"time":176000,"text":"that we happen to be atheists\nas well as evolutionists."},{"time":180302,"text":"They see us as rocking the boat,\nand you can understand why."},{"time":185689,"text":"Creationists, lacking any coherent\nscientific argument for their case,"},{"time":190442,"text":"fall back on the popular\nphobia against atheism:"},{"time":195420,"text":"Teach your children\nevolution in biology class,"},{"time":199000,"text":"and they'll soon move on to drugs,\ngrand larceny and sexual \"pre-version.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":204000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"In fact, of course, educated\ntheologians from the Pope down"},{"time":212000,"text":"are firm in their support of evolution."},{"time":214886,"text":"This book, \"Finding\nDarwin's God,\" by Kenneth Miller,"},{"time":217829,"text":"is one of the most effective attacks\non Intelligent Design that I know"},{"time":221916,"text":"and it's all the more effective because\nit's written by a devout Christian."},{"time":226000,"text":"People like Kenneth Miller could be called\na \"godsend\" to the evolution lobby,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":230606,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":232000,"text":"because they expose the lie\nthat evolutionism is, as a matter of fact,"},{"time":236751,"text":"tantamount to atheism."},{"time":238398,"text":"People like me, on the other\nhand, rock the boat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243175,"text":"But here, I want to say something\nnice about creationists."},{"time":246000,"text":"It's not a thing I often do,\nso listen carefully."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248700,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":250000,"text":"I think they're right about one thing."},{"time":253000,"text":"I think they're right that evolution"},{"time":255000,"text":"is fundamentally hostile to religion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258643,"text":"I've already said that many individual\nevolutionists, like the Pope,"},{"time":261881,"text":"are also religious, but I think\nthey're deluding themselves."},{"time":265460,"text":"I believe a true\nunderstanding of Darwinism"},{"time":268428,"text":"is deeply corrosive to religious faith."},{"time":273349,"text":"Now, it may sound as though\nI'm about to preach atheism,"},{"time":278596,"text":"and I want to reassure you\nthat that's not what I'm going to do."},{"time":282452,"text":"In an audience\nas sophisticated as this one,"},{"time":286000,"text":"that would be preaching to the choir."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288853,"text":"No, what I want to urge upon you --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":291497,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":295264,"text":"Instead, what I want to urge\nupon you is militant atheism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305222,"text":"But that's putting it too negatively."},{"time":308001,"text":"If I was a person who were interested\nin preserving religious faith,"},{"time":312674,"text":"I would be very afraid of the positive\npower of evolutionary science,"},{"time":317847,"text":"and indeed science generally,\nbut evolution in particular,"},{"time":320720,"text":"to inspire and enthrall,\nprecisely because it is atheistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328337,"text":"Now, the difficult problem\nfor any theory of biological design"},{"time":332114,"text":"is to explain the massive statistical\nimprobability of living things."},{"time":338000,"text":"Statistical improbability\nin the direction of good design --"},{"time":342796,"text":"\"complexity\" is another word for this."},{"time":345269,"text":"The standard creationist argument --"},{"time":347040,"text":"there is only one;\nthey're all reduced to this one --"},{"time":350000,"text":"takes off from\na statistical improbability."},{"time":352404,"text":"Living creatures are too complex\nto have come about by chance;"},{"time":355714,"text":"therefore, they must have had a designer."},{"time":358594,"text":"This argument of course,\nshoots itself in the foot."},{"time":361062,"text":"Any designer capable of designing\nsomething really complex"},{"time":364401,"text":"has to be even more complex himself,"},{"time":367006,"text":"and that's before we even start\non the other things he's expected to do,"},{"time":371000,"text":"like forgive sins, bless\nmarriages, listen to prayers --"},{"time":374938,"text":"favor our side in a war --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":379410,"text":"disapprove of our sex lives, and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"Complexity is the problem\nthat any theory of biology has to solve,"},{"time":389000,"text":"and you can't solve it by postulating\nan agent that is even more complex,"},{"time":393731,"text":"thereby simply compounding the problem."},{"time":396928,"text":"Darwinian natural selection\nis so stunningly elegant"},{"time":401349,"text":"because it solves the problem\nof explaining complexity"},{"time":405198,"text":"in terms of nothing but simplicity."},{"time":409094,"text":"Essentially, it does it\nby providing a smooth ramp"},{"time":412387,"text":"of gradual, step-by-step increment."},{"time":416757,"text":"But here, I only want to make the point"},{"time":418654,"text":"that the elegance of Darwinism\nis corrosive to religion,"},{"time":422368,"text":"precisely because it is so elegant,\nso parsimonious, so powerful,"},{"time":427000,"text":"so economically powerful."},{"time":431285,"text":"It has the sinewy economy\nof a beautiful suspension bridge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438000,"text":"The God theory is not just a bad theory."},{"time":440615,"text":"It turns out to be -- in principle --"},{"time":442409,"text":"incapable of doing the job required of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446464,"text":"So, returning to tactics\nand the evolution lobby,"},{"time":449599,"text":"I want to argue that rocking the boat"},{"time":452745,"text":"may be just the right thing to do."},{"time":458452,"text":"My approach to attacking creationism is --"},{"time":461072,"text":"unlike the evolution lobby --"},{"time":463579,"text":"my approach to attacking creationism\nis to attack religion as a whole."},{"time":469356,"text":"And at this point I need\nto acknowledge the remarkable taboo"},{"time":473642,"text":"against speaking ill of religion,"},{"time":476152,"text":"and I'm going to do so in the words\nof the late Douglas Adams,"},{"time":479525,"text":"a dear friend who,\nif he never came to TED,"},{"time":481788,"text":"certainly should have been invited."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483794,"text":"(Richard Saul Wurman: He was.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":485285,"text":"Richard Dawkins: He was. Good.\nI thought he must have been."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488332,"text":"He begins this speech,\nwhich was tape recorded in Cambridge"},{"time":491200,"text":"shortly before he died --"},{"time":493000,"text":"he begins by explaining how science\nworks through the testing of hypotheses"},{"time":497597,"text":"that are framed to be vulnerable\nto disproof, and then he goes on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501224,"text":"I quote, \"Religion doesn't\nseem to work like that."},{"time":505000,"text":"It has certain ideas at the heart of it,\nwhich we call 'sacred' or 'holy.'"},{"time":509000,"text":"What it means is:\nhere is an idea or a notion"},{"time":512000,"text":"that you're not allowed\nto say anything bad about."},{"time":515679,"text":"You're just not. Why not?\nBecause you're not.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":523928,"text":"\"Why should it be\nthat it's perfectly legitimate"},{"time":526373,"text":"to support the Republicans or Democrats,"},{"time":528386,"text":"this model of economics versus that,"},{"time":530770,"text":"Macintosh instead of Windows,"},{"time":532759,"text":"but to have an opinion\nabout how the universe began,"},{"time":535744,"text":"about who created the universe --"},{"time":537404,"text":"no, that's holy."},{"time":539784,"text":"So, we're used to not\nchallenging religious ideas,"},{"time":543174,"text":"and it's very interesting how much\nof a furor Richard creates"},{"time":546388,"text":"when he does it.\" --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":547571,"text":"He meant me, not that one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550578,"text":"\"Everybody gets absolutely\nfrantic about it,"},{"time":553000,"text":"because you're not allowed\nto say these things."},{"time":555612,"text":"Yet when you look at it rationally,"},{"time":557333,"text":"there's no reason why those ideas"},{"time":559453,"text":"shouldn't be as open\nto debate as any other,"},{"time":562152,"text":"except that we've agreed\nsomehow between us"},{"time":565245,"text":"that they shouldn't be.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":566983,"text":"And that's the end\nof the quote from Douglas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571864,"text":"In my view, not only is science\ncorrosive to religion;"},{"time":576000,"text":"religion is corrosive to science."},{"time":579698,"text":"It teaches people\nto be satisfied with trivial,"},{"time":583595,"text":"supernatural non-explanations,"},{"time":586642,"text":"and blinds them to the wonderful,\nreal explanations"},{"time":590397,"text":"that we have within our grasp."},{"time":592595,"text":"It teaches them to accept\nauthority, revelation and faith,"},{"time":598660,"text":"instead of always insisting on evidence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604081,"text":"There's Douglas Adams, magnificent picture\nfrom his book, \"Last Chance to See.\""},{"time":610000,"text":"Now, there's a typical scientific journal,"},{"time":612684,"text":"The Quarterly Review of Biology."},{"time":614341,"text":"And I'm going to put\ntogether, as guest editor,"},{"time":617221,"text":"a special issue on the question,\n\"Did an asteroid kill the dinosaurs?\""},{"time":622490,"text":"And the first paper\nis a standard scientific paper,"},{"time":626611,"text":"presenting evidence,"},{"time":628510,"text":"\"Iridium layer at the K-T boundary,"},{"time":630269,"text":"and potassium argon dated\ncrater in Yucatan,"},{"time":632714,"text":"indicate that an asteroid\nkilled the dinosaurs.\""},{"time":635349,"text":"Perfectly ordinary scientific paper."},{"time":638000,"text":"Now, the next one."},{"time":639557,"text":"\"The President of the Royal Society"},{"time":642246,"text":"has been vouchsafed\na strong inner conviction"},{"time":646758,"text":"that an asteroid killed the dinosaurs.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":649285,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":653530,"text":"\"It has been privately\nrevealed to Professor Huxtane"}]},{"cues":[{"time":659356,"text":"that an asteroid killed the dinosaurs.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":661301,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":664960,"text":"\"Professor Hordley was brought up"},{"time":667285,"text":"to have total and unquestioning faith\" --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"(Laughter) --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":671056,"text":"\"that an asteroid killed the dinosaurs.\""},{"time":678459,"text":"\"Professor Hawkins has\npromulgated an official dogma"},{"time":683000,"text":"binding on all loyal Hawkinsians"},{"time":686468,"text":"that an asteroid killed the dinosaurs.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":689361,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":692523,"text":"That's inconceivable, of course."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696848,"text":"But suppose --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":698102,"text":"[Supporters of the Asteroid Theory\ncannot be patriotic citizens]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":701172,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":702911,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":707774,"text":"In 1987, a reporter asked George Bush, Sr."},{"time":711000,"text":"whether he recognized\nthe equal citizenship and patriotism"},{"time":714842,"text":"of Americans who are atheists."},{"time":717000,"text":"Mr. Bush's reply has become infamous."},{"time":720000,"text":"\"No, I don't know that atheists\nshould be considered citizens,"},{"time":724000,"text":"nor should they be considered patriots."},{"time":726000,"text":"This is one nation under God.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":729571,"text":"Bush's bigotry\nwas not an isolated mistake,"},{"time":732214,"text":"blurted out in the heat\nof the moment and later retracted."},{"time":735523,"text":"He stood by it in the face of repeated\ncalls for clarification or withdrawal."},{"time":740394,"text":"He really meant it."},{"time":741648,"text":"More to the point, he knew\nit posed no threat to his election --"},{"time":746227,"text":"quite the contrary."},{"time":747433,"text":"Democrats as well as Republicans\nparade their religiousness"},{"time":751187,"text":"if they want to get elected."},{"time":752935,"text":"Both parties invoke\n\"one nation under God.\""},{"time":757119,"text":"What would Thomas Jefferson have said?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":759455,"text":"[In every country and in every age,\nthe priest has been hostile to liberty]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":763105,"text":"Incidentally, I'm not usually\nvery proud of being British,"},{"time":767000,"text":"but you can't help making the comparison."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":779485,"text":"In practice, what is an atheist?"},{"time":782000,"text":"An atheist is just somebody\nwho feels about Yahweh"},{"time":786332,"text":"the way any decent Christian feels\nabout Thor or Baal or the golden calf."},{"time":792619,"text":"As has been said before, we are\nall atheists about most of the gods"},{"time":797000,"text":"that humanity has ever believed in."},{"time":799329,"text":"Some of us just go one god further."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":805000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":812000,"text":"And however we define atheism,\nit's surely the kind of academic belief"},{"time":815358,"text":"that a person is entitled\nto hold without being vilified"},{"time":819000,"text":"as an unpatriotic,\nunelectable non-citizen."},{"time":824045,"text":"Nevertheless, it's an undeniable fact\nthat to own up to being an atheist"},{"time":827453,"text":"is tantamount to introducing yourself\nas Mr. Hitler or Miss Beelzebub."},{"time":832583,"text":"And that all stems\nfrom the perception of atheists"},{"time":836309,"text":"as some kind of weird, way-out minority."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840889,"text":"Natalie Angier wrote a rather\nsad piece in the New Yorker,"},{"time":844000,"text":"saying how lonely she felt as an atheist."},{"time":846420,"text":"She clearly feels\nin a beleaguered minority."},{"time":848882,"text":"But actually, how do American atheists\nstack up numerically?"},{"time":855000,"text":"The latest survey makes\nsurprisingly encouraging reading."},{"time":858296,"text":"Christianity, of course, takes a massive\nlion's share of the population,"},{"time":861750,"text":"with nearly 160 million."},{"time":864256,"text":"But what would you think\nwas the second largest group,"},{"time":867757,"text":"convincingly outnumbering Jews\nwith 2.8 million, Muslims at 1.1 million,"},{"time":873217,"text":"Hindus, Buddhists and all other\nreligions put together?"},{"time":876891,"text":"The second largest group,\nwith nearly 30 million,"},{"time":879558,"text":"is the one described\nas non-religious or secular."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883701,"text":"You can't help wondering\nwhy vote-seeking politicians"},{"time":887000,"text":"are so proverbially overawed by the power\nof, for example, the Jewish lobby --"},{"time":892206,"text":"the state of Israel seems to owe its very\nexistence to the American Jewish vote --"},{"time":896547,"text":"while at the same time,"},{"time":898000,"text":"consigning the non-religious\nto political oblivion."},{"time":903344,"text":"This secular non-religious vote,\nif properly mobilized,"},{"time":907000,"text":"is nine times as numerous\nas the Jewish vote."},{"time":911000,"text":"Why does this far more\nsubstantial minority"},{"time":914000,"text":"not make a move to exercise\nits political muscle?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":918285,"text":"Well, so much for quantity.\nHow about quality?"},{"time":921539,"text":"Is there any correlation,\npositive or negative,"},{"time":924666,"text":"between intelligence\nand tendency to be religious?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":928701,"text":"[Them folks misunderestimated me]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":930962,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":935582,"text":"The survey that I quoted,\nwhich is the ARIS survey,"},{"time":939000,"text":"didn't break down its data\nby socio-economic class or education,"},{"time":942072,"text":"IQ or anything else."},{"time":943818,"text":"But a recent article by Paul G. Bell\nin the Mensa magazine"},{"time":948000,"text":"provides some straws in the wind."},{"time":950000,"text":"Mensa, as you know,\nis an international organization"},{"time":952501,"text":"for people with very high IQ."},{"time":955835,"text":"And from a meta-analysis\nof the literature,"},{"time":960794,"text":"Bell concludes that, I quote --\n\"Of 43 studies carried out since 1927"},{"time":966000,"text":"on the relationship\nbetween religious belief,"},{"time":968319,"text":"and one's intelligence\nor educational level,"},{"time":970809,"text":"all but four found an inverse connection."},{"time":975000,"text":"That is, the higher one's intelligence\nor educational level,"},{"time":978641,"text":"the less one is likely to be religious.\""},{"time":981000,"text":"Well, I haven't seen\nthe original 42 studies,"},{"time":983199,"text":"and I can't comment on that meta-analysis,"},{"time":986231,"text":"but I would like to see more\nstudies done along those lines."},{"time":989968,"text":"And I know that there are --\nif I could put a little plug here --"},{"time":993055,"text":"there are people in this audience"},{"time":994675,"text":"easily capable of financing a massive\nresearch survey to settle the question,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"and I put the suggestion up,\nfor what it's worth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002609,"text":"But let me know show you some data"},{"time":1004283,"text":"that have been properly\npublished and analyzed,"},{"time":1006536,"text":"on one special group --\nnamely, top scientists."},{"time":1011444,"text":"In 1998, Larson and Witham\npolled the cream of American scientists,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"those who'd been honored by election\nto the National Academy of Sciences,"},{"time":1020715,"text":"and among this select group,"},{"time":1023370,"text":"belief in a personal God dropped\nto a shattering seven percent."},{"time":1030000,"text":"About 20 percent are agnostic;\nthe rest could fairly be called atheists."},{"time":1034771,"text":"Similar figures obtained\nfor belief in personal immortality."},{"time":1038000,"text":"Among biological scientists,\nthe figure is even lower:"},{"time":1041000,"text":"5.5 percent, only, believe in God."},{"time":1044779,"text":"Physical scientists, it's 7.5 percent."},{"time":1048000,"text":"I've not seen corresponding\nfigures for elite scholars"},{"time":1051000,"text":"in other fields,\nsuch as history or philosophy,"},{"time":1054000,"text":"but I'd be surprised\nif they were different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1057491,"text":"So, we've reached a truly\nremarkable situation,"},{"time":1060738,"text":"a grotesque mismatch\nbetween the American intelligentsia"},{"time":1065777,"text":"and the American electorate."},{"time":1068364,"text":"A philosophical opinion\nabout the nature of the universe,"},{"time":1072000,"text":"which is held by the vast majority\nof top American scientists"},{"time":1076000,"text":"and probably the majority\nof the intelligentsia generally,"},{"time":1079880,"text":"is so abhorrent to the American electorate"},{"time":1082704,"text":"that no candidate for popular election\ndare affirm it in public."},{"time":1088077,"text":"If I'm right, this means that high office"},{"time":1091000,"text":"in the greatest country in the world"},{"time":1093670,"text":"is barred to the very people\nbest qualified to hold it --"},{"time":1097781,"text":"the intelligentsia --"},{"time":1099000,"text":"unless they are prepared\nto lie about their beliefs."},{"time":1102000,"text":"To put it bluntly:\nAmerican political opportunities"},{"time":1105518,"text":"are heavily loaded against those"},{"time":1108000,"text":"who are simultaneously\nintelligent and honest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1110809,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1112039,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1118374,"text":"I'm not a citizen of this country,\nso I hope it won't be thought unbecoming"},{"time":1122000,"text":"if I suggest that something\nneeds to be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1125000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1127524,"text":"And I've already hinted\nwhat that something is."},{"time":1130000,"text":"From what I've seen of TED, I think this\nmay be the ideal place to launch it."},{"time":1134479,"text":"Again, I fear it will cost money."},{"time":1136654,"text":"We need a consciousness-raising,"},{"time":1139225,"text":"coming-out campaign for American atheists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1143000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1145000,"text":"This could be similar to the campaign\norganized by homosexuals"},{"time":1148744,"text":"a few years ago,"},{"time":1150000,"text":"although heaven forbid\nthat we should stoop to public outing"},{"time":1153357,"text":"of people against their will."},{"time":1155000,"text":"In most cases, people who out themselves"},{"time":1158000,"text":"will help to destroy the myth that\nthere is something wrong with atheists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1162000,"text":"On the contrary,"},{"time":1163177,"text":"they'll demonstrate that atheists\nare often the kinds of people"},{"time":1166271,"text":"who could serve as decent\nrole models for your children,"},{"time":1169000,"text":"the kinds of people an advertising agent\ncould use to recommend a product,"},{"time":1173791,"text":"the kinds of people\nwho are sitting in this room."},{"time":1178000,"text":"There should be a snowball effect,\na positive feedback,"},{"time":1181000,"text":"such that the more names\nwe have, the more we get."},{"time":1184590,"text":"There could be non-linearities,\nthreshold effects."},{"time":1187383,"text":"When a critical mass has been obtained,"},{"time":1189486,"text":"there's an abrupt\nacceleration in recruitment."},{"time":1192415,"text":"And again, it will need money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1195494,"text":"I suspect that the word \"atheist\" itself"},{"time":1199000,"text":"contains or remains a stumbling block"},{"time":1202491,"text":"far out of proportion\nto what it actually means,"},{"time":1205191,"text":"and a stumbling block to people"},{"time":1206788,"text":"who otherwise might be\nhappy to out themselves."},{"time":1209869,"text":"So, what other words might\nbe used to smooth the path,"},{"time":1212618,"text":"oil the wheels, sugar the pill?"},{"time":1216382,"text":"Darwin himself preferred \"agnostic\" --"},{"time":1219404,"text":"and not only out of loyalty\nto his friend Huxley,"},{"time":1222532,"text":"who coined the term."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1224733,"text":"Darwin said, \"I have never been an atheist"},{"time":1227590,"text":"in the same sense of denying\nthe existence of a God."},{"time":1230796,"text":"I think that generally an 'agnostic'"},{"time":1233000,"text":"would be the most correct\ndescription of my state of mind.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1236846,"text":"He even became uncharacteristically\ntetchy with Edward Aveling."},{"time":1242259,"text":"Aveling was a militant atheist"},{"time":1244000,"text":"who failed to persuade Darwin"},{"time":1246000,"text":"to accept the dedication\nof his book on atheism --"},{"time":1249000,"text":"incidentally, giving rise\nto a fascinating myth"},{"time":1251714,"text":"that Karl Marx tried to dedicate\n\"Das Kapital\" to Darwin,"},{"time":1255135,"text":"which he didn't, it was\nactually Edward Aveling."},{"time":1257527,"text":"What happened was that Aveling's\nmistress was Marx's daughter,"},{"time":1262000,"text":"and when both Darwin and Marx were dead,"},{"time":1265305,"text":"Marx's papers became muddled\nup with Aveling's papers,"},{"time":1269543,"text":"and a letter from Darwin saying,\n\"My dear sir, thank you very much"},{"time":1273874,"text":"but I don't want you\nto dedicate your book to me,\""},{"time":1276261,"text":"was mistakenly supposed\nto be addressed to Marx,"},{"time":1279538,"text":"and that gave rise to this whole\nmyth, which you've probably heard."},{"time":1282879,"text":"It's a sort of urban myth, that Marx\ntried to dedicate \"Kapital\" to Darwin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1287442,"text":"Anyway, it was Aveling, and when\nthey met, Darwin challenged Aveling."},{"time":1294682,"text":"\"Why do you call yourselves atheists?\""},{"time":1302148,"text":"\"'Agnostic, '\" retorted Aveling, \"was\nsimply 'atheist' writ respectable,"},{"time":1306459,"text":"and 'atheist' was simply\n'agnostic' writ aggressive.\""},{"time":1310292,"text":"Darwin complained, \"But why\nshould you be so aggressive?\""},{"time":1314141,"text":"Darwin thought that atheism might be\nwell and good for the intelligentsia,"},{"time":1317761,"text":"but that ordinary people were\nnot, quote, \"ripe for it.\""},{"time":1321857,"text":"Which is, of course, our old friend,\nthe \"don't rock the boat\" argument."},{"time":1326000,"text":"It's not recorded whether Aveling told\nDarwin to come down off his high horse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1331000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1332851,"text":"But in any case,\nthat was more than 100 years ago."},{"time":1335225,"text":"You'd think we might have\ngrown up since then."},{"time":1338129,"text":"Now, a friend, an intelligent lapsed Jew,"},{"time":1343417,"text":"who, incidentally, observes the Sabbath\nfor reasons of cultural solidarity,"},{"time":1347566,"text":"describes himself\nas a \"tooth-fairy agnostic.\""},{"time":1352066,"text":"He won't call himself an atheist"},{"time":1353653,"text":"because it's, in principle,\nimpossible to prove a negative,"},{"time":1357000,"text":"but \"agnostic\" on its own might\nsuggest that God's existence"},{"time":1360000,"text":"was therefore on equal terms\nof likelihood as his non-existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1365166,"text":"So, my friend is strictly\nagnostic about the tooth fairy,"},{"time":1369507,"text":"but it isn't very likely, is it?"},{"time":1372524,"text":"Like God."},{"time":1374000,"text":"Hence the phrase, \"tooth-fairy agnostic.\""},{"time":1376329,"text":"Bertrand Russell made the same point"},{"time":1378115,"text":"using a hypothetical teapot\nin orbit about Mars."},{"time":1382138,"text":"You would strictly have to be agnostic"},{"time":1384000,"text":"about whether there is a teapot\nin orbit about Mars,"},{"time":1386453,"text":"but that doesn't mean you treat\nthe likelihood of its existence"},{"time":1389477,"text":"as on all fours with its non-existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1392305,"text":"The list of things which we strictly\nhave to be agnostic about"},{"time":1395634,"text":"doesn't stop at tooth fairies\nand teapots; it's infinite."},{"time":1399000,"text":"If you want to believe\none particular one of them --"},{"time":1401501,"text":"unicorns or tooth fairies\nor teapots or Yahweh --"},{"time":1405605,"text":"the onus is on you to say why."},{"time":1408000,"text":"The onus is not on the rest\nof us to say why not."},{"time":1412000,"text":"We, who are atheists,"},{"time":1413406,"text":"are also a-fairyists and a-teapotists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1416821,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1419486,"text":"But we don't bother to say so."},{"time":1421843,"text":"And this is why my friend\nuses \"tooth-fairy agnostic\""},{"time":1425693,"text":"as a label for what most people\nwould call atheist."},{"time":1428679,"text":"Nonetheless, if we want to attract\ndeep-down atheists to come out publicly,"},{"time":1434122,"text":"we're going to have find\nsomething better to stick on our banner"},{"time":1437235,"text":"than \"tooth-fairy\" or \"teapot agnostic.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1440643,"text":"So, how about \"humanist\"?"},{"time":1444580,"text":"This has the advantage of a worldwide\nnetwork of well-organized associations"},{"time":1449000,"text":"and journals and things already in place."},{"time":1451000,"text":"My problem with it is only\nits apparent anthropocentrism."},{"time":1453972,"text":"One of the things\nwe've learned from Darwin"},{"time":1456002,"text":"is that the human species is only one"},{"time":1458502,"text":"among millions of cousins,\nsome close, some distant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1462330,"text":"And there are other possibilities,\nlike \"naturalist,\""},{"time":1464887,"text":"but that also has problems of confusion,"},{"time":1467346,"text":"because Darwin would have\nthought naturalist --"},{"time":1469576,"text":"\"Naturalist\" means, of course,\nas opposed to \"supernaturalist\" --"},{"time":1472735,"text":"and it is used sometimes --"},{"time":1474123,"text":"Darwin would have been confused\nby the other sense of \"naturalist,\""},{"time":1477541,"text":"which he was, of course,"},{"time":1478756,"text":"and I suppose there might be others\nwho would confuse it with \"nudism\"."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1483772,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1485014,"text":"Such people might be those\nbelonging to the British lynch mob,"},{"time":1491936,"text":"which last year attacked a pediatrician\nin mistake for a pedophile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1497000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1502549,"text":"I think the best of the available\nalternatives for \"atheist\""},{"time":1505733,"text":"is simply \"non-theist.\""},{"time":1507000,"text":"It lacks the strong connotation\nthat there's definitely no God,"},{"time":1510024,"text":"and it could therefore easily be embraced\nby teapot or tooth-fairy agnostics."},{"time":1515907,"text":"It's completely compatible\nwith the God of the physicists."},{"time":1521462,"text":"When atheists like Stephen Hawking\nand Albert Einstein use the word \"God,\""},{"time":1528000,"text":"they use it of course\nas a metaphorical shorthand"},{"time":1531737,"text":"for that deep, mysterious part of physics\nwhich we don't yet understand."},{"time":1537221,"text":"\"Non-theist\" will do for all that,\nyet unlike \"atheist,\""},{"time":1542261,"text":"it doesn't have the same\nphobic, hysterical responses."},{"time":1549558,"text":"But I think, actually, the alternative"},{"time":1551436,"text":"is to grasp the nettle\nof the word \"atheism\" itself,"},{"time":1554309,"text":"precisely because it is a taboo word,"},{"time":1557000,"text":"carrying frissons of hysterical phobia."},{"time":1561214,"text":"Critical mass may be harder\nto achieve with the word \"atheist\""},{"time":1564670,"text":"than with the word \"non-theist,\""},{"time":1566249,"text":"or some other non-confrontational word."},{"time":1568685,"text":"But if we did achieve it\nwith that dread word \"atheist\" itself,"},{"time":1572471,"text":"the political impact\nwould be even greater."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1576343,"text":"Now, I said that if I were religious,\nI'd be very afraid of evolution --"},{"time":1579772,"text":"I'd go further: I would fear science\nin general, if properly understood."},{"time":1583430,"text":"And this is because\nthe scientific worldview"},{"time":1586667,"text":"is so much more exciting, more poetic,"},{"time":1589756,"text":"more filled with sheer wonder"},{"time":1592257,"text":"than anything in the poverty-stricken\narsenals of the religious imagination."},{"time":1599237,"text":"As Carl Sagan, another recently\ndead hero, put it,"},{"time":1604000,"text":"\"How is it that hardly any major\nreligion has looked at science"},{"time":1608590,"text":"and concluded, 'This\nis better than we thought!"},{"time":1612909,"text":"The universe is much bigger\nthan our prophet said,"},{"time":1615405,"text":"grander, more subtle, more elegant'?"},{"time":1618636,"text":"Instead they say, 'No, no, no!"},{"time":1621000,"text":"My god is a little god,\nand I want him to stay that way.'"},{"time":1626179,"text":"A religion, old or new,"},{"time":1628333,"text":"that stressed the magnificence\nof the universe"},{"time":1631000,"text":"as revealed by modern science,"},{"time":1633000,"text":"might be able to draw forth\nreserves of reverence and awe"},{"time":1636688,"text":"hardly tapped by the conventional faiths.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1641220,"text":"Now, this is an elite audience,"},{"time":1644380,"text":"and I would therefore expect\nabout 10 percent of you to be religious."},{"time":1650904,"text":"Many of you probably subscribe\nto our polite cultural belief"},{"time":1655407,"text":"that we should respect religion."},{"time":1658303,"text":"But I also suspect\nthat a fair number of those"},{"time":1662000,"text":"secretly despise religion as much as I do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1665769,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1667052,"text":"If you're one of them, and of course\nmany of you may not be,"},{"time":1669929,"text":"but if you are one of them,"},{"time":1671261,"text":"I'm asking you to stop being polite,"},{"time":1673353,"text":"come out, and say so."},{"time":1676113,"text":"And if you happen to be rich,"},{"time":1678136,"text":"give some thought to ways\nin which you might make a difference."},{"time":1682369,"text":"The religious lobby in this country"},{"time":1684763,"text":"is massively financed by foundations --\nto say nothing of all the tax benefits --"},{"time":1690317,"text":"by foundations, such as the Templeton\nFoundation and the Discovery Institute."},{"time":1695515,"text":"We need an anti-Templeton to step forward."},{"time":1700793,"text":"If my books sold as well\nas Stephen Hawking's books,"},{"time":1704000,"text":"instead of only as well as\nRichard Dawkins' books, I'd do it myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1711454,"text":"People are always going on about,\n\"How did September the 11th change you?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1718871,"text":"Well, here's how it changed me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1721469,"text":"Let's all stop being so damned respectful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1726380,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1728000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}